"co-naissance," from Valéry came "implex" or the "animal of words" and the "chiasma of two destinies." Literature also provokes the questions of expression, metaphor, and truth and the meaning of a Merleau-Pontian poetics.The poetic of Merleau-Ponty is, the book argues, a poetic of the flesh, a poetic of mystery, and a poetic of the visible in its relation to the invisible. Ultimately, theoretical figures or "figuratives" that appear at the threshold between philosophy and literature enable the possibility of a new ontology. What is at stake is the very meaning of philosophy itself and its mode of expression.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh  aHeidegger.  aHusserl.  aPaul Claudel.  aPaul Valéry.  aProust.  aSartre.  aWalter Benjamin.  ametaphor.  aontology.  aphenomenology.1 aCarbone, Mauro, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCarbone, Mauro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Galen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaint Aubert, Emmanuel de, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 ade Saint Aubert, Emmanuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311072271040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/97808232